President Trump's Director of Legislative Affairs, Marc T. Short, has announced several additions to the Legislative Affairs House staff team. These individuals have extensive experience and relationships on Capitol Hill, and they will be valuable in advancing the President's agenda. Jonathan Hiler will serve as Assistant to the Vice President and Director of Legislative Affairs, while Joyce Meyer will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President and House Deputy Director of Legislative Affairs. Alex Angelson, Ben Howard, Tim Pataki, Cindy Simms, and Paul Teller will all serve as Special Assistants to the President and House Special Assistants.